article.description: — Curtis Jones scored 22 points as Buffalo beat Canisius 86-66 on Sunday night.
article.headline: Jones' 22 help Buffalo beat Canisius 86-66
article.story: BUFFALO, N.Y. -- — Curtis Jones scored 22 points as Buffalo beat Canisius 86-66 on Sunday night. Jones also contributed six rebounds and five steals for the Bulls (3-4). Zid Powell added 14 points and five rebounds. Armoni Foster recorded 12 points. Jamir Moultrie finished with 17 points for the Golden Griffins (2-4). Tahj Staveskie added nine points, seven rebounds and five assists for Canisius. Jordan Henderson finished with nine points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
